Meet The Town of Lake Placid
Administration
The Town Administration and Staff are available to assist both residents and non-residents of Lake Placid with their needs.  Their extensive experience in serving the public is a testament to their commitment to continuous improvement and ensuring that every interaction is a positive one. You can count on them to handle your needs with care, professionalism, and a focus on achieving the best possible outcome.
Town Administrator  Charlette Rodriguez
Contact:  Phone:863-699-3747 ext 119
Email
Charlette Rodriguez brings extensive leadership experience in both the public and private sectors, with a proven track record of effective management and accomplishments in local government. Throughout her career, she has successfully navigated significant challenges, including public health crises and disaster recovery efforts, demonstrating resilience and strategic leadership.   As the Town Administrator, Charlette is committed to enhancing the community's quality of life and success while embracing the challenges and opportunities that come with this crucial role. She leverages her experience in citizen engagement, financial management, strategic planning, human resources, public communication, and building relationships with community stakeholders and staff. Guided by a strong sense of integrity and empathy, she is dedicated to serving the community effectively.
Town Clerk
Contact:  Phone:863-699-3747 ext 107
Email
Eva Cooper-Hapeman is a skilled professional with experience in both the private and public sectors. She has worked as a Systems Administrator/Manager in the private sector and for the Highlands County Economic Development Commission in the public sector. Eva relocated to the Town of Lake Placid in 2004 after discovering the area.  As the Town Clerk for the Town of Lake Placid since 2013, Eva is committed to ensuring transparency in all town matters. She manages the town's public records and responds to any public inquiries and requests. Eva also documents all public meetings and ensures that the public is notified of all town meetings.
Director of Finance
Contact:  Phone:863-699-3747 ext 103
Email
​
​
Rachel Osborne is a lifetime resident of Lake Placid and has been working with the Town since February 2004. Her main responsibility is to oversee financial activities such as reporting on revenue, administering the budget, training accounting staff, conducting internal audits, disbursing funds to departments, and establishing financial procedures. In addition, Rachel supervises the functions of the Front Desk, Customer Service, Utility Billing, Account Payable, Fixed Asset, and Payroll within the Finance Department. She also plays a key role in human resource functions and employee-benefit programs.
Lake Placid Police Department
Contact:  Phone: 863-699-3757
Email
Chief Schneider was sworn in as Chief of police on June 2, 2023.  After graduation from Lake Placid High School, he joined the United States Navy being discharged honorably after completing his tour of duty.  He began his career with the Lake Placid Police Department in September of 1998.  Climbing the ranks until being sworn in as Chief of Police. Chief Schneider received his Bachelor of Applied Science degree from South Florida State College.
Town Planner
Contact:
Phone:863-699-3747 ext 127
Email
​
Dana Riddell has been working in zoning and planning since 2016. She started working with Highlands County and then moved on to the Central Florida Regional Planning Council. Dana was born and raised in a small town outside of Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. She relocated to Lake Placid in 2013 and has been living in Highlands County ever since. Dana holds a bachelor's degree from South Florida State College and is responsible for the day-to-day operations of the Planning Department.
Public Works Director
Alan Keefer
Phone:863-699-3747 ext 202
Email
Town Property Maintenance Director Harry Durbano
Phone:863-699-3747
Email

​
Welcome to Town!
​
Nestled in natural beauty, Lake Placid is a Town where both residents and visitors can enjoy the simple pleasures of life. From indulging in delicious meals at local eateries to taking a stroll through one of the parks, there is something for everyone.
With its two unique nicknames, "Town of Murals" and "The Caladium Capital of the World", Lake Placid is a place where art and nature come together in perfect harmony. Its rich history, dating back to 1927, is a testament to the Town's spirit of innovation and progress. Reader's Digest named Lake Placid America's Most Interesting Town in 2013, and it's easy to see why.
The Town has it all, and it invites you to come and experience its charm for yourself.
